This paper discusses the impact of learning rate schedules on the performance of deep learning models, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the optimization behavior of deep networks during training, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep networks in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE), which are all relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the effects of different learning rate schedules on model generalization, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
